Joseph PerkinsVice President - General Counsel & Secretary at NIBCO Inc.LocationElkhart, IndianaIndustryConstructionCurrentNIBCO INC.PreviousCummins Inc., Cummins IncEducationUniversity of Virginia School of Law500+ connectionsView Joseph’s full profile. It's free!Your colleagues, classmates, and 500 million other professionals are on LinkedIn.View Joseph’s Full ProfileJoseph’s ActivityI am very happy and blessed to be celebrating a lucky 7...Joseph likedHappy 4th of July from NIBCO!Joseph likedTBT 1970s: Cleaning and sorting operation at Elkhart wrot...Joseph likedNIBCO is committed to creating fun experiences for...Joseph likedHappy Father's Day from NIBCO!Joseph likedThe Building Materials Foundation fundraising event was...Joseph likedSee all activitySummaryMr. Perkins has more than 20 years of experience as an in-house counsel. He has responsibility for all legal matters for NIBCO Inc. and he is corporate secretary. In his previous role with Cummins Inc. he had two main areas of responsibility. As Deputy General Counsel for the Americas, he supervised company legal services throughout the Americas across Cummins four business units. As Legal Quality Champion, he was responsible for driving continuous improvement to Law Department processes across the globe to ensure that the Cummins Law Department delivers world class legal services. For more than a decade, he held leadership roles with two business units as their Chief Legal Counsel.His skill sets include being a strategic business counselor to business unit Presidents and business segment leaders.  He is also a disciplined negotiator of non-U.S. joint ventures in several countries, and he has been lead counsel on numerous negotiations of large OEM supply agreements. He was also lead counsel for Cummins during the Chrysler bankruptcy, negotiating a favorable result for Cummins. Perkins has a significant amount of exerience in trade issues and trade relations, with a heavy focus on trade relations between the United States and Brazil. He has participated in trade missions to Brazil, and led the briefing at Brazil's Foreign Ministry regarding the bilateral tax treaty negotiation between the United States and Brazil.  He has a significant amount of experience with global trade compliance issues, including export control regulations, the Foreign Corrupt Practices Act, and prohibited substances regulations.  He has represented Cummins before Customs officials in other countries. Perkins has a significant amount of experience recruiting, coaching and developing talented global legal teams. He manages a talented team of attorneys who represent Cummins throughout the Americas. His direct reports include lawyers in the United States, Mexico and Brazil.ExperienceVice President - General Counsel & SecretaryNIBCO INC.June 2015  –  Present (2 years 2 months)Founded in 1908, NIBCO Inc. is a leading provider of valves, fittings and flow control products for commercial, industrial and institutional construction, as well as residential and irrigation markets. NIBCO has ten manufacturing plants located throughout the United States, Mexico and Poland. Deputy General Counsel for the Americas and Legal Quality ChampionCummins Inc.March 2014  –  May 2015 (1 year 3 months)Supervise company legal services throughtout North America, Central America and South America across the four Business Units with lawyers and legal teams based in the United States, Mexico and Brazil. Responsible for driving continuous improvement to Law Department processes across the globe to ensure that the Cummins Law Department delivers consistent world class legal services.Senior Counsel - Engine BusinessCummins Inc.2008  –  February 2014 (6 years)Chief legal counsel for the $11 Billion flagship business unit of Cummins •	Serve on business unit Leadership Team as legal advisor to the Business Unit President and business segment leaders. •	Supervise legal work for the Business Unit around the globe, managing internal and external counsel on a broad range of transactions and issues.•	Lead counsel for the negotiation of new joint venture formations, contracts with large OEM customers, and other high level strategic legal issues.•	Organized and led the Cummins team which managed the company’s recovery following the high profile Chapter 11 petition filed by key customer, Chrysler. The team’s work resulted in no financial loss to Cummins.   Legal advisor to Cummins representative on Unsecured Creditors Committee. •	Manage high exposure litigation matters for the Business Unit around the globe.•	Manage direct reports in the United States, Brazil and Mexico.Senior Counsel - Power Generation BusinessCummins Inc2003  –  2008 (5 years)Dual role as chief legal counsel for Power Generation Business Unit and for Cummins Latin America•	Serve on business unit Leadership Team as legal advisor to the Business Unit President and business segment leaders. This Leadership Team turned a struggling business into a company producing more than $2 Billion in revenues and significant PBIT contribution to the overall success of Cummins Inc. •	Supervise legal work for the Business Unit around the globe, managing internal and external counsel on a broad range of transactions and issues.•	Lead counsel responding to informal inquiry by the Securities and Exchange Commission, which resulted in no fines and a minor books and records infraction. •	Lead counsel for divestiture of non-core businesses, and contracts with largest customers•	Standardized supply contracts for Purchasing function and trained Purchasing Department on contract negotiation using standardized contract•	Manage high exposure litigation matters for the Business Unit around the globe. •	Manage direct reports in the United States and Brazil.•	Trained business unit leadership team on U.S. Foreign Corrupt Practices Act and U.S. Export Controls regulations•	Supervise all legal matters in Mexico and Latin America for Cummins Inc. •	Recruited and developed Latin American legal team.  •	Supervise strategy for litigation matters in Latin America, particularly Brazil.SkillsIntellectual PropertyLitigationStrategyCorporate GovernanceJoint VenturesCorporate LawStrategic PlanningCommercial LitigationNegotiationLegal IssuesLeadershipEmployment LawContract NegotiationLegal WritingFinanceSee 7+ManagementSix SigmaRecruitingMergers & AcquisitionsPolicyCross-functional Team LeadershipGovernmentSee lessHow's this translation?Great•Has errorsThanks for your help!Honors & AwardsTop Assistant General CounselFirst ChairMay 2012Honorary Secretary of StateIndiana Secretary of State Sue Anne GilroyJuly 2002Awarded Honorary Secretary of State for being the longest serving member of the Indiana Election Commission in Indiana History.  Appointed by two Governors.Business Turn Around AwardCummins Power Generation President and Cummins Inc. CEONovember 2006Awarded for legal work, and advice and counsel, contributing directly to the turn around of a failing subsidiary and the sale of the subsidiary for a profit.Chairman's Quality AwardCummins Inc. CEO and Chairman2004Legal advisor to, and member of, Six Sigma team awarded Chairman's Quality Award for a project which resulted in significant process improvement and reduced operating costs.Cummins Inc Leadership Culture SeriesCummins Inc.2011Graduated from Cummins Leadership Culture Series, leadership development course.Volunteer Experience & CausesCoachCarmel Dads Club Special SportsChildrenFor almost a decade, I have been a coach for the Special Sports program. Our program provides sports activities for children with physical and developmental disabilities from age 5 through young adulthood. Volunteer Chair of Tax Litigation Task ForceBrazil-U.S. Business CouncilChair of Tax Litigation Task Force - Focused on ways to mitigate tax litigation risk for U.S. companies conducting business in Brazil. Trade Missions to Brasilia - participated in trade missions to Brasilia in 2007 and 2008. Led Bilateral Tax Treaty briefing at Brazil's Foreign Ministry.Lead Private Sector StaffU.S. - Brazil CEO Forum2007  –  2009 (2 years)Managed private sector participation in the U.S.-Brazil CEO Forum, which my CEO was Chair of. Organized and managed two meetings per year of 20 CEOs and high level government officials from the U.S. and Brazilian governments.Causes Joseph cares about:Arts and CultureEconomic EmpowermentEducationPoliticsScience and TechnologyLanguagesEnglishNative or bilingual proficiencyPortugueseElementary proficiencyEducationUniversity of Virginia School of LawJ.D., LawJ.D., Law1986  –  1989Activities and Societies: President - Student Bar AssociationPrinceton UniversityA.B., Department of PoliticsA.B., Department of Politics1982  –  1986GroupsIn The House:  The Professional Networking Community For In-House Counsele-LEGAL In-House: Corporate & General Counsel, Lawyers & AttorneysIn The House: General CounselCorporate CounselINHOUSE LEGAL - General Counsels, CLO's, In House Lawyers, General Counsele-LEGALIvyLife PrincetonSee 5 moreACC Brazil Networking GroupOnce a General Counsel, Always a General CounselIvy League AlumniGeneral Counsel NewsInsideCounselSee lessView Joseph’s full profile to...See who you know in commonGet introducedContact Joseph directlyView Joseph’s Full ProfileNot the Joseph you’re looking for? View moreView this profile in another languageEnglishGermanPeople Also ViewedMary HuserSenior Vice President, General Counsel and Corporate SecretaryTom EiseleSenior Vice President & Chief Legal Officer at NIBCO Inc.Meredith (Emerson) RitchieVice President, General Counsel & Chief Ethics OfficerChristopher EckSVP - Legal & Human Resources, General Counsel & Corporate Secretary at Finish LineAtiba AdamsGeneral CounselSheryll CashinProfessor of Law;  Author, Loving: Interracial Intimacy and the threat to White Supremacy (Beacon 2017)Bob SwahnProgram Manager, Nuclear Technologies at Defense Threat Reduction AgencyRegina WarrenSr Human Resource Gener